sting rights demands in universalistic terms, while leveraging their standing as representatives of growing minority populations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aPressure groupszUnited States. 4aPolicy. 4aPolitics -- United States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / National.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107042040 cprintz978080475175940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780804767750?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804767750423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804767750/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles